[tool-call] end id=call_PLSssunvYytWnLlNdDrf0nRP|fc_07944b9078291de0016a275a7447b08193a210c96a2efd7dd0 name=edit args={"path": "tests/src/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/src/test/java/org_mozilla/rhino/TypeInfoTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.net.URLStreamHandler;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;\n", "newText": "import java.net.URLStreamHandler;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.mozilla.classfile.ByteCode;\nimport org.mozilla.classfile.ClassFileWriter;\n", "newText": "import org.mozilla.classfile.ByteCode;\nimport org.mozilla.classfile.ClassFileWriter;\n\nimport sun.misc.Unsafe;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void mergesDifferentObjectTypesWhenGeneratingStackMap() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            assertThat(exerciseStackMapMergeWithJava6ClassFileVersion())\n                    .isEqualTo(\"generated/TypeInfoMerge\");\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static String exerciseStackMapMergeWithJava6ClassFileVersion() throws Exception {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void mergesDifferentObjectTypesWhenGeneratingStackMap() throws Exception {\n        StackMapGenerationSwitch stackMapGenerationSwitch = enableStackMapGeneration();\n        try {\n            assertThat(generateMergedObjectStackMapClass())\n                    .isEqualTo(\"generated/TypeInfoMerge\");\n        } finally {\n            stackMapGenerationSwitch.close();\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void mergesDifferentObjectTypesWithJava6ClassFileResource() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            assertThat(exerciseStackMapMergeWithJava6ClassFileVersion())\n                    .isEqualTo(\"generated/TypeInfoMerge\");\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static String generateMergedObjectStackMapClass() {\n        return new StackMapMergeExercise().call();\n    }\n\n    private static StackMapGenerationSwitch enableStackMapGeneration() throws Exception {\n        ClassFileWriter warmup = new ClassFileWriter(\n                \"generated/TypeInfoWarmup\", \"java/lang/Object\", null);\n        assertThat(warmup.getClassName()).isEqualTo(\"generated/TypeInfoWarmup\");\n\n        Unsafe unsafe = unsafe();\n        Field generateStackMap = ClassFileWriter.class.getDeclaredField(\"GenerateStackMap\");\n        Object base = unsafe.staticFieldBase(generateStackMap);\n        long offset = unsafe.staticFieldOffset(generateStackMap);\n        boolean previous = unsafe.getBoolean(base, offset);\n        unsafe.putBoolean(base, offset, true);\n        return new StackMapGenerationSwitch(unsafe, base, offset, previous);\n    }\n\n    private static Unsafe unsafe() throws Exception {\n        Field unsafe = Unsafe.class.getDeclaredField(\"theUnsafe\");\n        unsafe.setAccessible(true);\n        return (Unsafe) unsafe.get(null);\n    }\n\n    private static String exerciseStackMapMergeWithJava6ClassFileVersion() throws Exception {\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Ensuring field initialization**\n\nI need to be careful with the `Unsafe.staticFieldBase` because it might not initialize correctly. Before setting a `Field` object for static final, I need to make sure the class is initialized, or the field won't have a value. It’s important to ensure everything is set up right so that the field exists with a valid value. I'll double-check this to avoid any potential issues!\n\n**Considering test implementation**\n\nI need to implement a separate test for merging, possibly using the original. There’s an existing test with the same name, so I might replace the child loader or add a new one if the file size allows. I should check if any imports are unused and consider adding `import java.lang.reflect.Field; import sun.misc.Unsafe;`. I have to check the import order according to Checkstyle: usually, it's alphabetical, with Java before org and sun after. I'll write the necessary edits!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_07944b9078291de0016a275a4f63108193941befb32296e88b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJ1p0_Y57lIhU8tVv4NX2YHoVMWSWhxxZLGRDjnIbTyambyw_h6eV2sx-c3OcHtTSf1CtxmsrOW50gmK1ZFec01pEHrQVuX-FYn8HpXA1tSed47Y2o8BgOCMm_ap-u74fuvWcJpwNtJFUwg47tjvIgWr8gLARbEIePXLZymuYV86Mh627slhy6BxWReGeXlK6QWFQ-KCn8Bb3p-TSs_7lfie_oCYsp2MmxF578szoUt3_kXzuEzc1hYVYwDh-5DQi1r6xN25CR-Be8YmBTaOSD0ZR2-ejUSTtUzakJsNghYMo2fHKXvEmYr4moA8fPY9ruIaPpPafXCfxnXg7qRJWULvxioVRYin426JewgH99mn0D9IDZFfFOc8edNFZVilrcLLKJB2ekwJzk4bk8SF8pozT4uu4HCrSwa_7eRaRvqaoJWe7CQmm0SPhZPesBmZFyn_NW7oDocAh57S-vB7JzXpuBLTL9tsFfGyErxEPL9vmA1i5AulG3mMkSD0KCcXfvlAyD--pwnko6A9Dgnlsl_8ZaMf2tQ_VnFm1UXqzO6z79CbZGNuMNlING82arZT3ih-s587S3cPybXZaCHLrPVulXCWRyBxlSMc7GUMEtUIZV7k0JrgCVLTtRROSLEaKJYObPIV4aj2FqgW2g__0bd_kobTbYJY5mtLZwOhhsT1hiPs9KR_H2LGU7Hsa0sWwBnV_u60kuLaXl5NZAw2Q7M_V6feDgmHKTXofOzvwp48pnwol2tyttw0qe1rcDYXNhVuwBmKlG6aStdFcggX6IFR3fqNd-j